The structure of the EU FLW data flows represented as percentage shares by different leverage points along the supply chain (Fig. 5
                           ), is supported using official FLW quantity estimates from Eurostat (2023a). To summarise, the largest share of EU FLW (64 %) is generated by households (far right column, Fig. 6
                           ). At the EU level, post-harvest losses, food processing and retail and distribution losses account for 11 %, 18 % and 7 % of total FLW, respectively. There is, however, variation across member states, where for example Bulgaria, Denmark, Netherlands and Spain exhibit a majority of FLW corresponding to the stages of industrial food production. Further consideration of this data is given in Sections 4 and 5.
